title.78: Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi (1993) #5

description.0: When a power core failure deactivates the security system at the mansion, Sabretooth attacks. And he has Jubilee in his sights!
description.5: The final chapter in the strange, twisted saga of Peter's parents! Richard and Mary Parker learn the true identity of Spider-Man, prompting them to report to "their master." Tragedy awaits the wall-crawler, as all is not as it seems.
description.6: The NYPD accuses Sersi of murder, despite Black Knight's confirmation of her innocence. In a moment of distress, will Sersi be able to control her rage? And who will be the victim is she loses all control?
description.7: Omega Red is on a murderous rampage, and to stop him Cable must team up with...the Acolytes of Magneto!? But what is Omega Red after? And can Cable even trust the Acolytes not to betray him?
description.9: The X-Force battles Fitzroy on the Guthrie's farm! Meanwhile, the Gamemaster's plans develop further when he draws all other teams into a trap thinking they're going to be saving the mutants in the Gamemaster's possession…
description.11: Wong becomes Salome’s new servant! Doctor Strange must recover the “Coral Crab” from a Leviathan.
description.15: Are Heaven and Hell in cahoots? Daimon suspects just that when the Asura, angel assassins, hunt down two heretical devotees. The Armorer is still at large, and Hellstorm doesn't have a second to waste.
description.20: In the'Star Wars'galaxy, automatons are so much necessary property, but even first-degree'droids'are considered expendable! Set before the events of'Star Wars: A New Hope'and the formation of the'Empire,'Droids'features the adventures of'protocol droid'See-Threepio'and'astromech droid'Artoo-Detoo'in the'Kalarba system. Despite their differences, See-Threepio and Artoo-Detoo know that the best way to survive is to stick together. Thank the maker!
description.24: Silver Surfer and Legacy must pacify the monks of the Oracle’s monastery. Will Thanos ever return what is not rightfully his? No chance! The battle for all-encompassing knowledge just got heated.
description.25: When the X-Force and New Warriors try and free their captured friends from the Gamemaster, they are sucked into his elaborate plans as well! Can the Gamemaster really take down FOUR mutant teams with ONE twisted game?
description.28: Adam Warlock attempts to restore the memories of his teammate Maxam, using the infinity Gems! But first, he'll have to travel to Monster Isle, and fight a bloodthirsty group of mind-controlled Avengers!
description.32: Marvel Comics Presents the many faces of Typhoid Mary! What really goes on inside the head of Marvel's most deranged? Wolverine tracks down Typhoid to seek her help in saving a mutant empath. A new personality, Bloody Mary, emerges.
description.33: Matt Murdock's "death" means a new beginning for Daredevil! But it's a new beginning for evil as well, as the assault team known as System Crash makes its move! Before they can strike, however, they'll have to take out the man standing in their way- the Sentinel of Liberty himself, Captain America!
description.35: Stranded in space! Hulk and Silver Surfer have lost the trail of Trauma and Atalanta after a dizzying hyperspace jump! Good thing the noble space pirate crew known as the Starjammers arrives to lend a hand!
description.36: You won't want to miss this action-packed issue. It's Iron Man versus Venom! Who will win?
description.40: Thor returns to Earth where he knows he belongs! While there, he fights off a swarm of monsters, all with the same all-too-familiar master!
description.42: Don't miss this blockbuster 100th issue! A core team member perishes despite Haven's best intentions. As Haven's doomsday fast approaches, Havok holds his team together by their seams!
description.44: The tremors of STARBLAST continue to rock the Marvel Universe! The FF and Namor come face to face with the mastermind behind the Earth shiffting, but can they overcome the mysterious Xlyym?
description.45: Cyclops and Cable battle the X-Cutioner!
description.47: The Wedding of Jean Grey and Scott Summers! After years of tragedy and torment, death and rebirth, Cyclops and Marvel Girl finally say “I do”!!” And it’s cause for not just celebration but also reflection as Professor X takes stock of how far his dream has come and how his original students have grown. The X-Men’s X-tended friends and family descend on the mansion to join the festivities — but a longtime ally’s absence is deeply missed. Will the wedding go as planned? Can the X-Men finally relax and be happy? And once the vows are exchanged and the first dance is over, who will catch the bouquet?
description.50: Spider-Man's been robbed of his youth! In a twist of weird science, the Vulture restores his youth by stealing years from Peter Parker! Plus, will Spidey reveal his secret identity to his parents?
description.51: Four Avengers investigate why a tracking station in Scotland has disrupted signals. Back at the mansion, Quicksilver attempts to reconcile with Crystal, while Sersi undergoes therapy with the Black Knight. Will Sersi finally be cured of her debilitating madness?
description.52: Enter THE KILLING FIELD! Cable has just learned the truth of his family ties, and he'll do whatever it takes to get more answers- unless the villainous Omega Red has his way! Can Cable defeat this Cold War killing machine?
description.55: Thanos pulls a bait and switch on the Secret Defenders! And now, Doctor Strange has been deposed as leader! The Oracle of Ancient Knowledge proves to be a highly valued android. But will the monks who possess this artificial intelligence do down peacefully? Rhino and Super-Skrull are about to find out…the hard way!
description.56: The Gamemaster has his clan, the Upstarts, find and kill off former Hellions and New Mutants as part of a sick and twisted game. Will the former heroes be able to keep up with the game's ever changing rules to ensure their survival?
description.60: While the rest of the team are desperate to find them- Sam, Boomer, and Magma are stuck in a sick and twisted game by the Gamemaster. Will X-Force interrogating the Guthrie family be enough to save their teammates?
description.64: Dr. Stevens pulls off another party, while Morbius tracks Strange down to his new Sanctum Sanctorum.
description.66: The race is on between Gambit, the Assassins, and the Thieves' Guild to claim the Elixir of Life! Meanwhile, Rogue reveals her amorous feelings for Remy, while his family banishes him from New Orleans!
description.76: Avram Siegel requires justice for a life struck down too soon. Hellstorm seeks to deliver.
description.78: Will Bogga the Hutt claim his prize and will Nomi be able to complete her Jedi training?
description.81: The Watch vs. Thanos! Meanwhile, Odin does his best to cure Thor of his insanity, but his efforts prove in vain.
description.83: Elektra lives! Hellspawn strikes! Morbius hungers! The Snakeroot and Daredevil have their final showdown as everything comes to a head!
description.85: It's the Incredible Hulk - in space! Trauma has kidnapped Hulk's friend Atalanta, and intends to take her to the far reaches of the universe! Can even the aid of the Silver Surfer help Hulk make it in time?
description.86: Tony Stark is under fire for a number of criminal charges committed Stark Enterprises. Just when things can't get any worse, Deathlok attacks!
description.88: What is it like to be rescued by an Angel? Powerful and uplifting, the imagery and symbolism in this cover speak for themselves. Alex Ross' unique style captures this moment of salvation in simply incredible fashion.
description.91: Odin enters the psyche of Thor to release the Thunder God from his mental chains.
description.93: Rahne is at last cured of her psychic connection to Havok, and her lupine state. X-Factor takes on Haven directly, but are deeply conflicted when she claims to still be an ally to their cause.
description.95: Journey to the deep! Back up to full strength, the FF head to the depths of the ocean to discover what is causing devastating shifts in the Earth's crust! Guest-starring Namor, the Sub-Mariner!
description.96: Turn the pages of a secret chapter of Professor X's life...

3.text: The Chameleon continues to elude Spider-Man despite the Wall-Crawler’s best efforts to extract information. Then, a breakthrough...

8.text: The fight between the X-Men and the Freakshow trudges on! And the X-Men learn about Avalon, a place where many mutants have been taken for protection.

9.text: The X-Force battles Fitzroy on the Guthrie's farm! Meanwhile, the Gamemaster's plans develop further when he draws all other teams into a trap thinking they're going to be saving the mutants in the Gamemaster's possession…

11.text: Wong becomes Salome’s new servant! Doctor Strange must recover the “Coral Crab” from a Leviathan.

13.text: War Machine’s first issue in his 1994 ongoing series! First on the agenda? War Machine must take on Eda Arul and the Advisor! Plus, revelations about James Rhodes, the man behind the armored suit.

14.text: In the midst of a perilous "Paradise Detour," Luke continues his hunt for the missing S'ybll, while being pursued by what appears to be his old foe, the Night Beast. Eventually, the mystery of the successive unexplained appearances of Tanith Shire, the Night Beast, and Ben Kenobi is solved, and as it turns out, S'ybll has some very sinister, and selfish, plans for the young Jedi. Needless to say, Luke escapes S'ybll's clutches, after another Rebel rescue just in the nick of time. He, along with our other Rebel heroes, finally arrive at the new Rebel base on Hoth, ready for "A New Beginning." They're greeted there by a perturbed Princess Leia, who, before they can so much as look around, has another potentially dangerous mission for the unflappable Luke, Han, and Chewie.

16.text: What could cause Storm to attack Rogue!?

17.text: Venom (Eddie Brock) and the Hulk make for a pretty great battle, but will an Earthquake threat from Dr. Bad Vibes prove to be the bigger problem?

18.text: Spider-Man and Beast, captives of the Brand Corporation! Plus, what happens when the Hobgoblin comes to possess the mutant-creating serum pioneered by Brand?

19.text: It all comes down to this! Hawkeye and his new ally Rover have their final showdown with the Secret Empire!

21.text: Master Pandemonium has one more trick up his sleeve! Scarlet Witch faces off against a fellow Nexus Being by the name of Lore. But why does Lore look identical to Scarlet Witch? Reality is threatened with a re-write as Wanda’s darkest nature is channeled through this new enemy!

23.text: Has Thanos found a comrade in arms with Terrax? The warrior from Lanlak certainly shares a bloodlust with the mad Titan, especially for Tyrant, Galactus’ android. This could be the beginning of Marvel’s most dangerous alliance yet!

24.text: Silver Surfer and Legacy must pacify the monks of the Oracle’s monastery. Will Thanos ever return what is not rightfully his? No chance! The battle for all-encompassing knowledge just got heated.

25.text: When the X-Force and New Warriors try and free their captured friends from the Gamemaster, they are sucked into his elaborate plans as well! Can the Gamemaster really take down FOUR mutant teams with ONE twisted game?

26.text: Will the Beyonder prove victorious in his battle with Mephisto? The fate of Protégé hangs in the delicate balance.

27.text: Mayoral candidate Charles Palentine proves to be harboring a dark secret. Venom and Morbius vs. Demogoblin and his entire goblin army!

28.text: Adam Warlock attempts to restore the memories of his teammate Maxam, using the infinity Gems! But first, he'll have to travel to Monster Isle, and fight a bloodthirsty group of mind-controlled Avengers!

29.text: See Silver Surfer, through the eyes and lens of Photographer Phil Sheldon. Witness the coming of the world-devouring Galactus in Book III of Marvels.  Can the Fantastic Four stop Galactus before he destroys the planet?

30.text: Spider-Man 2099 dumped in Downtown! After an unsuccessful confrontation with imposter Thor, Spidey finds himself cursing his involvement in the battle for Valhalla. The Aesir battle for Mjolnir, but who is truly worthy? Plus, Doom 2099 pulls the wool over everyone’s eyes with a shocking coup!

31.text: FIGHTING CHANCE BOOK 1 It all starts here! Witness the most startling event in the life of America's greatest hero as Cap battles for his life!

32.text: Marvel Comics Presents the many faces of Typhoid Mary! What really goes on inside the head of Marvel’s most deranged? Wolverine tracks down Typhoid to seek her help in saving a mutant empath. A new personality, Bloody Mary, emerges.

38.text: Everyone descends on the small town of Laastekist hunting for the Punisher.

46.text: Wolverine's deadliest foes continue to test the newly vulnerable Logan. Now, Cyber has turned up to take his piece of Logan.

47.text: Over 30 years after meeting as two of Professor Xavier's first students, Cyclops and Jean Grey finally tied the knot. The only one not celebrating? Poor old "I've got a crush on Jean" Wolverine.

53.text: Master Pandemonium transforms the West Coast Avengers into demonic beasts…and Scarlet Witch must pick up the pieces! Can Wanda Maximoff save her teammates from themselves? Pandemonium professes his undying love, leaving Scarlet Witch more determined than ever to eradicate her most dangerous foe.

54.text: Thanos takes extreme measures to relieve his boredom- measures that involve mass murder! The cosmos tremble as the tyrant searches for a worthy combatant. Enter the cosmic playing field of Marvel’s mightiest galactic heroes! Who will be able to stop the Mad Titan?

55.text: Thanos pulls a bait and switch on the Secret Defenders! And now, Doctor Strange has been deposed as leader! The Oracle of Ancient Knowledge proves to be a highly valued android. But will the monks who possess this artificial intelligence do down peacefully? Rhino and Super-Skrull are about to find out…the hard way!

56.text: The Gamemaster has his clan, the Upstarts, find and kill off former Hellions and New Mutants as part of a sick and twisted game. Will the former heroes be able to keep up with the game's ever changing rules to ensure their survival?

57.text: The Beyonder and Mephisto duke it out to claim the Protégé!

58.text: Venom and Morbius team up against a goblin invasion! Demogoblin ascends as a power player.

59.text: Flashback to WWII! Captain America and Bucky must find Baron Zemo before his new deadly weapon wipes out the US Air Force!

64.text: Dr. Stevens pulls off another party, while Morbius tracks Strange down to his new Sanctum Sanctorum.

65.text: With the help of the local sheriff, Punisher kills almost everyone who has chased him to the town of Lastekist; Lynn and Payback recover from injuries and decide to quit the Punisher game; Micro hooks up with Mickey and decides to try and rebuild his Punisher program with someone new.

67.text: Introducing... The Freakshow! The X-Men come across a woman called Mama Hurricane, who was a member of the mutant underground railroad. Xi'an hopes she many know of any underground mutant communities that may be still in existence.

68.text: The real Punisher is back in action…and he's ready to end the chaos of his doppelgangers.

69.text: A sensational team-up, both on and off the page! In this historic crossover between newspaper strip and comic book, Spider-Man and the Beast join forces to take down the Hobgoblin - with the fate of mutantkind in the balance!

70.text: Hawkeye gets an all-new costume to help him take the fight to the Secret Empire! Plus, he gets a helping hand from none other than WAR MACHINE!

71.text: Mort is in for the fight of his life when he takes on Death! Can this dead teenager win his freedom?

72.text: THE FALL OF THE HAMMER PART 2 The X-Men of 2099 pay Ravage a visit. What will lead the X-Men to the hallowed halls of Valhalla? And will they uncover the truth about missing scientist Jordan Boone? Ravage may have the answer to this question and more!

73.text: As the Rebels manage to escape the wrath of Darth Vader and the Imperials while escaping to Hoth, they discover that the Millennium Falcon didn't make it out of hyperspace. Crippled by a malfunctioning navigational computer, Luke Skywalker and friends land on the nearest planet, a veritable tropical paradise, to make repairs. Luke soon runs into a woman appearing to be Tanith Shire under attack from a carnivorous plant, and uses the Force to get out of a tight jam. But what's Tanith Shire doing alone on this mysterious outlying planet? The young Rebel is about to find out the real story behind "The Paradise Detour."

74.text: Darkhawk and Venom continue their alliance to rescue Mike Powell. Ultimately, the ill-fated hero, Darkhawk, gets swept into space by the devious St. Johnny.

75.text: The Fantastic Four pay Namor a visit in the wake of Llyra’s deceit.

77.text: The X-Men vs. The Nasty Boys!

79.text: THE FALL OF THE HAMMER PART 1 Has Thor truly returned to 2099? If so, the God of Thunder has lost his sense of honor! Spider-Man must take down an imposter Thor, and protect Dana from becoming a “sport of the gods”!

80.text: Will Thor's mind be restored with the help of...Thanos?!

81.text: The Watch vs. Thanos! Meanwhile, Odin does his best to cure Thor of his insanity, but his efforts prove in vain.

88.text: What is it like to be rescued by an Angel?  Powerful and uplifting, the imagery and symbolism in this cover speak for themselves.  Alex Ross' unique style captures this moment of salvation in simply incredible fashion.

News Photographer Phil Sheldon, takes on the task of reporting a story about New York City's very own super heroes.  A book giving a glimpse at modern day legends! Follow The Avengers from a new perspective, and experience shot-by-shot a tale that may just end up to be more for than the cameraman bargained for.

89.text: Presumed dead, Frank Castle skips town. Along the way, he meets a little girl whose father is a cop. How long can Punisher hide out in a tree house??

90.text: Spider-Man and Iron Fist must prevent Platoon and his army from taking over the entire city. OUTNUMBERED AND OUTGUNNED, CAN THEY STOP THE ONE MAN KILLING MACHINE??

97.text: Bloodscream hunts a vulnerable Wolverine. Can Logan survive against the fully-powered monster that is Bloodscream?

98.text: A Hellfire Club party becomes a deathtrap for the team!
